<% external_link_classes = "min-w-0 font-semibold wrap-anywhere underline hover:decoration-2 focus-visible:outline-hidden focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus-visible:rounded-sm dark:text-white" %>

<div class="container mx-auto space-y-8 px-4 py-8">
  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="accessibility-statement-title">
    <h1 id="accessibility-statement-title" class="text-heading text-5xl font-bold">Accessibility statement</h1>

    <p class="text-body text-lg">
      Accessibility Standards Canada aims to meet the highest standard of accessibility. We follow the Government of
      Canada's
      <a href="https://www.tbs-sct.gc.ca/pol/doc-eng.aspx?id=23601" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">Standard on Web Accessibility<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>.
      This standard follows the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C)
      <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>
      (WCAG) 2.0.
    </p>

    <p class="text-body text-lg">
      This site will work to meet the guidelines from
      <a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI/intro/wcag" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1 AA<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>.
      This sets a higher standard.
    </p>

    <p class="text-body text-lg">
      This statement highlights our efforts to improve accessibility. We know it is important to have an inclusive
      website that is accessible to everyone.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="standards-compliance-title">
    <h2 id="standards-compliance-title" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Standards compliance</h2>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>All pages on this site meet WCAG 2.0 or higher.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="aria-landmarks-title">
    <h2 id="aria-landmarks-title" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">ARIA Landmarks</h2>

    <p class="text-body text-lg">
      ARIA stands for Accessible Rich Internet Applications Suite. It defines a way to make Web content and Web
      applications more accessible to people with disabilities.
    </p>

    <p class="text-body text-lg">
      This website makes use of
      <a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI/intro/aria.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">ARIA<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>
      mark-up that makes it easier to identify the major sections and roles on each page. A screen reader will choose
      major landmarks on the page such as:
    </p>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>the content area,</li>

      <li>navigation mechanisms, and</li>

      <li>the search area.</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-body text-lg">
      The
      <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria/#landmark_roles" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">ARIA landmarks<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>
      used include:
    </p>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>Search</li>

      <li>Navigation</li>

      <li>Main</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="images-title">
    <h2 id="images-title" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Images</h2>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>All images on this web site have alternative text descriptions.</li>

      <li>Our content is usable or accessible without images.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="links-title">
    <h2 id="links-title" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Links</h2>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>
        We do our best to have links written so that they make sense out of context. If this is not possible, we add a
        title attribute or other type of search aid to create context.
      </li>

      <li>
        The first link in every document is the default "Skip to main content" link. This allows the user to skip
        directly to the main section of the page (the content).
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="forms-title">
    <h2 id="forms-title" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Forms</h2>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>All form controls are appropriately and clearly labelled.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="visual-design-title">
    <h2 id="visual-design-title" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Visual design</h2>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>
        This site uses only relative font sizes. These are compatible with the user-chosen "text size" option in visual
        browsers.
      </li>

      <li>
        This site uses a high contrast colour scheme. The colours used meet the minimum contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for
        normal text and 3:1 for large text.
      </li>

      <li>
        This site does not use colour alone to convey information. For example, required form fields are indicated with
        an asterisk in addition to being coloured red.
      </li>

      <li>
        This site does not use flashing or blinking content. This is to avoid triggering seizures in people with
        photosensitive epilepsy.
      </li>

      <li>This site can be resized up to 200% without loss of content or functionality.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="accessibility-tools-title">
    <h2 id="accessibility-tools-title" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Accessibility tools</h2>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>
        <a href="http://www.nvda-project.org/wiki/Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">NVDA<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>
        a free, open-source screen reader (Windows)
      </li>

      <li>
        <a href="http://www.satogo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">System Access<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>
        (Windows)
      </li>

      <li>
        <a href="http://www.freedomscientific.com/jaws-hq.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">JAWS<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>
        (Windows)
      </li>

      <li>
        <a href="https://www.apple.com/voiceover/info/guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">VoiceOver<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>
        (Mac)
      </li>

      <li>
        <a href="https://orca.gnome.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">Orca<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>
        (Linux)
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="accessibility-guidelines-title">
    <h2 id="accessibility-guidelines-title" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">
      Accessibility guidelines and related resources
    </h2>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>
        <a
          href="http://www.webaim.org/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="<%= external_link_classes %>"
        >
          WebAIM<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a
          href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="<%= external_link_classes %>"
        >
          W3 accessibility guidelines<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="feedback-title">
    <h2 id="feedback-title" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">
      Tell us how we're doing
    </h2>

    <p class="text-body text-lg">
      We are always happy to get feedback from you. We need it to be sure our website meets the highest level of
      accessibility. If you have trouble, questions or suggestions about the accessibility of our website, please
      <a href="mailto:gsp-psg@phac-aspc.gc.ca" class="
        min-w-0 font-semibold wrap-anywhere underline hover:decoration-2 focus-visible:rounded-sm
        focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus-visible:outline-hidden dark:text-white
      ">contact us</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>
